        public boolean isSuperType(DfType other)
        Description copied from interface: DfType
        Checks whether this type is the supertype of the supplied type, i.e. every value from the other type belongs to this type as well. if A.isSuperType(B) then A.join(B) is A and A.meet(B) is B.
